    "faq_FdPmxb": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "text_BKLRkc": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the recommended starting dose of mad honey? ",
            "answer": "<p>For the first time, we advised starting with just 1- 2 teaspoons of approximately 2.5gm. This small dose allows you to understand your body's reactions to grayanotoxins. Most experienced users typically consume between 1-2 teaspoons around 5-10gm, but individual tolerance varies on body type, age and weight. Always wait at least 30-60 minutes before considering additional amounts and see how your body reacts.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_U4YDGc": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do I know if I am taking too much mad honey?",
            "answer": "<p>Mostly, the signs of excessive mad honey consumption include dizziness, nausea, low blood pressure, excessive sweating, and, in rare cases, temporary heart rhythm changes. If you ever experience any of these symptoms, stop and consult a healthcare professional. Start with small amounts and slowly increase based on your body type.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_9qeeXW": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I mix mad honey with other foods or drinks?",
            "answer": "<p>You can mix it with warm tea, spread it on toast, or mix it into yogurt. Avoid mixing with hot beverages, as high temperatures can degrade the beneficial compounds of honey. Many customers messaged us that mixing with herbal tea enhances the effects while diluting the strong flavor.  Make sure not to mix mad honey with any alcoholic drinks or psychedelic substances.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_gD3fmP": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does body weight affect mad honey dosage?",
            "answer": "<p>Body weight significantly matters how mad honey affects you. Our calculator accounts for this by recommending approximately 0.05g of mad honey per kilogram of body weight for beginners. A person weighing 70kg (154 lbs) might start with 3.5gm, while someone weighing 90kg (198 lbs) might start with 4.5gm.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_C7LX9q": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long should I wait between doses of mad honey?",
            "answer": "<p>Always wait at least 3-4 hours between doses. Mad honey's effects typically peak within 1-2 hours and can last 3-6 hours, depending on individual metabolism. We recommend limiting consumption to once daily and taking at least 2-3 days off per week to prevent body tolerance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_tp7K6E": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is the dosage different for medicinal v/s recreational use?",
            "answer": "<p>Therapeutic benefits like anti-inflammatory effects or digestive support, start with small daily doses of 1 to 2 teaspoons are typically good. For more pronounced effects, 2-3 teaspoons may be appropriate for experienced users but should never be exceeded.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_WKJBKM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does mad honey potency vary between seasons?",
            "answer": "<p>Mostly spring harvested mad honey typically contains 3 times higher grayanotoxin concentration than autumn harvests. Our calculator factors in seasonal potency variations, recommending lower doses for spring-harvested products. All our products are from spring harvest season so start with a small dose.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_DDXcFA": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I develop a tolerance to mad honey?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes, the regular consumers may develop tolerance to mad honey effects. More than an effect , honey has amazing health benefits which you can enjoy for life time.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
