          "settings": {
            "title": "Seasonal Differences:",
            "subtitle": "",
            "description": "<p>The grayanotoxin concentration in mad honey varies significantly by harvest season based on the flowering time of rhododendron and wildflowers. </p><p>Spring Harvest : In Nepal, usually in April- June the honey is  more potent due to higher rhododendron nectar concentration as it is the peak flowering season. Start with less dose when consuming spring harvested mad honey.</p><p>Autumn Harvest : In September -November generally milder with more balanced grayanotoxin levels as it's not the flowering time of rhododendron. Start with a high dose calibrated for autumn harvested honey.<br/><br/></p>",
            "button_text": "",
            "button_link": "",
            "button_text_2": "",
            "button_link_2": ""
          }
        },
