          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Regional Variations:",
            "subtitle": "",
            "description": "<p>Geographic origin significantly impacts mad honey's potency: </p><p></p><ul><li>Geographic origin significantly impacts mad honey's potency:Nepal (Himalayan Region ):  Nepal is the only place on earth where we can find the most potent, with high concentrations of grayanotoxins from R. luteum and R. ponticum. Use the nepal sourced mad honey wisely. </li><li>Turkey (Black Sea Region): Turkey regions usually produce moderate potency, primarily from R. ponticum. Your calculated dose is calibrated for Turkish mad honey.</li><li>Other Regions: Not so popular and available in local regions of Georgia, India, China and Bhutan. No scientific research and availability of higher concentrations of grayanotoxins.  </li><li>Potency varies widely. Start with small dose until you understand the specific characteristics.</li><li>Product Note: All our mad honey products are available from Nepal from spring harvest only choose the nepal region to adjust your dosage accordingly. When in doubt, email us , we will be happy to guide you.</li></ul>",
            "button_text": "",
            "button_link": "",
